@startuml req-session-lifecycle
skinparam backgroundColor White
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor LightBlue
  BorderColor Navy
  FontColor Black
  ArrowColor DarkBlue
}

[*] --> not_started : Agent created\n(no tmux pane, no Claude session)

not_started --> starting : User starts group\nor individual agent\n[pre-assign session UUID]

starting --> active : Claude CLI ready\nin tmux pane\n[session UUID stored in SQLite]

starting --> degraded : Claude fails to start\nwithin 3 seconds\n[exit code non-zero]

active --> paused : User clicks Pause (P)\nor agent calls pause_agent()\n[pub/sub events buffered ≤ 50]

paused --> active : User clicks Resume (R)\n[drain pending_events in order]

active --> stopping : User stops agent\nor Group Stop All\nor session exits normally\n[Stop hook fires → publishes agent.stopped]

stopping --> stopped : Claude exits cleanly\nor tmux kill-pane after 5s timeout\n[session status updated in SQLite]

stopped --> starting : User restarts agent\nor Group Resume\n[use --resume <uuid> if session ID valid]

degraded --> starting : User clicks Re-attach / Restart

active --> degraded : tmux pane lost externally\n(killed outside platform)\n[supervisor detects missing pane]

note right of active
  pub/sub events delivered
  claude --session-id <uuid> running
  tmux capture-pane refresh active
  MCP tools available to agent
end note

note right of paused
  Claude session still running
  User can type directly in pane
  Pub/sub events buffered (max 50)
  MCP publish_event still works
end note

note right of stopped
  tmux pane destroyed
  Session UUID preserved in SQLite
  Resume will use --resume <uuid>
  Or start fresh if UUID expired
end note
@enduml
